article.headline: South Alabama 90, North Texas 89, OT
article.story: MOBILE, Ala. (AP) -- Demetric Bennett led all scorers with 29 points and Daon Merritt had 24 in South Alabama's 90-89 overtime victory over North Texas on Sunday. It was the eighth straight win for South Alabama (15-7, 9-2 Sun Belt Conference). North Texas (14-7, 5-5 SBC) was led by Quincy Williams, with 19 points and 11 rebounds. North Texas led 49-45 at halftime. The score was 81-81 going into overtime. Merritt tied the game at 89 with one minute left in overtime. After a turnover by North Texas, South had the ball with 33.3 seconds left and played for the last shot. Merritt drove to the hoop and dished to sophomore Brandon Davis who was fouled with 3.8 seconds left. Davis went to the line for two shots and made one for a 90-89 lead. UNT put the ball in play and Ben Bell forced a desperation 3-pointer from half court that did not go in.
